text.section:
For the purpose of enforcing the provisions of this chapter, officers, agents, and inspectors of the board shall have the power and authority to:
Administer oaths;
Enter upon premises of all facilities issued a permit or license by the board, at all reasonable times for the purpose of:
Making inspections and carrying out the provisions of this chapter;
Conducting investigations;
Requiring production of books, papers, documents, records, or other evidence for inspection or copying;
Seizing evidence; or
Securing oral or written statements;
Employ special investigators;
Expend funds for the purpose of obtaining evidence; and
Issue subpoenas.
